	# 🔥 Q2) Can we inherit (extend) a record?

	## ❌ No, you CANNOT extend a record

	---

	## 🔥 Reason 1: Record is already extending a class

	```java
	record Employee(int id) {}
	```

	Internally:

	```java
	final class Employee extends java.lang.Record
	```

	👉 Java allows:

	> Only **one class inheritance**

	---

	## 🔥 Reason 2: Record is `final`

	👉 Compiler makes it:

	```java
	final class Employee
	```

	### ❌ So this is illegal:

	```java
	class Manager extends Employee {}  // ❌ ERROR
	```

	---

	## 🔥 Reason 3 (DEEP CONCEPT)

	Inheritance means:

	> "I can change or extend behavior"

	But record means:

	> "Fixed structure, fixed data"

	👉 These two ideas conflict.

	---

